parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank can cause the fuel system to become clogged, leading to engine stalling, loss of power, and potential engine damage.
The failure of the head gasket can cause engine coolant to leak into the engine, leading to overheating, engine damage, and potential engine failure.
The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, slip, or stall, leading to potential accidents or engine damage.
symptoms: and unusual noises from the transmission.

symptoms: and unusual noises from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust system can cause the vehicle to lose power, overheat, and potentially fail.

The failure of the electrical system, specifically the wiring harness, can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents. Additionally, it can lead to electrical fires, which can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially harm occupants.
